getShortName().Description: Localized short display name for the level, e.g. "1". Returns an empty string if no shortName is defined.

activate().Description: Sets this level as the visible level in its building. If a level is enclosed in several buildings, then all those buildings will have this level set as active.

getName().Description: Localized display name for the level, e.g. "Ground floor". Returns an empty string if no name is defined.

ClassDesc: Represents a level in a building. IndoorLevel objects are only equal by id. It is possible that may have different contents. While a level is usually enclosed by a single building, a level might be enclosed by several buildings (e.g., a carpark level might span multiple buildings).
